An Act relative to license transparency.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Subsection (b) of section 7 of chapter 81 of the Acts of 2022 is hereby amended by
2 inserting after the words “regulations promulgated by the attorney general;”, in the second to last
3 sentence the following words:
4 said regulations shall, at a minimum, require the registrar of motor vehicles to provide
5 information on the holder of a Massachusetts license (1) to any city or town clerk seeking to
6 verify the identity and eligibility of any individual using a Massachusetts license to vote or to
7 register to vote and (2) in response to a request from any state law enforcement agency pursuant
8 to an investigation.
